Mandla Maseko, selected to be the first black African to go into space, has passed away before realising his dream. Courtesy of #DSTV403 JOHANNESBURG - Tributes are pouring on social media for Mandla 'Spaceboy' Maseko, who was selected to be the first black African to go into space. Maseko's family said in a statement that he had died in a motorcycle accident on Saturday night. READ: Mandla 'Spaceboy' Maseko dies before reaching the stars In 2014, Maseko became one of 23 people who won a seat on an hour-long sub-orbit trip. The trip was sponsored by the Apollo Space Academy. South Africans took to social media on Monday to pay tribute to the 30-year-old private pilot from Soshanguve, describing his loss as a great tragedy for the country.